BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 104.64 600 Td (Chapter 11: Managing Finances) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Keep your business finances separate from personal accounts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Open a dedicated bank account for your Etsy income and expenses.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Track every expense including materials, shipping, and Etsy fees.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Save receipts for tax deductions related to your business.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Set aside 25 to 30 percent of profits for taxes if you are in the US.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Use accounting software like Wave \(free\) or QuickBooks to track finances.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Understand that Etsy deposits payments on a regular schedule.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Review your Etsy payment account regularly for accuracy.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Calculate your true profit after all fees, materials, and time investment.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Reinvest some profits back into your business for growth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Consult a tax professional once your income becomes significant.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Plan for seasonal fluctuations in income throughout the year.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (11) Tj ET

