BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 89.28 600 Td (Chapter 12: Scaling Your Business) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Scaling means growing your revenue without proportionally increasing work.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Identify your bestselling items and create variations of those products.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Streamline your production process to make items faster.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Consider hiring help for packaging, shipping, or production tasks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Batch similar tasks together for efficiency in your workflow.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Add digital products that can be sold unlimited times with no extra work.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Expand to complementary product lines that appeal to existing customers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Raise prices as demand grows rather than trying to sell more at low prices.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Invest in better tools and equipment to improve production speed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Consider expanding to other platforms like your own website or Amazon Handmade.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Automate repetitive tasks like social media posting and inventory tracking.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Set revenue goals and create action plans to reach each milestone.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (12) Tj ET

endstream
